thread.title: Unemployment rate rises to 6%

title: Unemployment rate rises to 6%
text:
Australia's unemployment rate climbed to 6 per cent in June. Photo: Jeffrey Chan
Australia's unemployment rate climbed to 6 per cent in June, from a revised 5.9 per cent in May, according to the Australian Bureau of Statistics.
The ABS said on Thursday the number of people employed rose by 7300 to 11.77 million, seasonally adjusted.
However, the participation rate also rose, from 64.7 per cent to 64.8 per cent.
Despite the small increase in the headline unemployment figure, markets welcomed the news.
Advertisement Economists had expected a jump from the unrevised 6 per cent figure in May to 6.1 per cent in June.
The Australian dollar, which had been trading up ahead of the data release, spiked to US74.42¢ before quickly easing back to US74.09¢.
